#: of numpy.bartlett:36
msgid "The Bartlett window is defined as"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.bartlett:38
msgid ""
"w(n) = \\frac{2}{M-1} \\left(\n"
"\\frac{M-1}{2} - \\left|n - \\frac{M-1}{2}\\right|\n"
"\\right)\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.bartlett:42
msgid ""
"Most references to the Bartlett window come from the signal processing "
"literature, where it is used as one of many windowing functions for "
"smoothing values.  Note that convolution with this window produces linear "
"interpolation.  It is also known as an apodization (which means \"removing "
"the foot\", i.e. smoothing discontinuities at the beginning and end of the "
"sampled signal) or tapering function. The Fourier transform of the Bartlett "
"window is the product of two sinc functions. Note the excellent discussion "
"in Kanasewich [R3a7a5a2c0d2a-2]_."
msgstr ""

